    <text>
        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
                <p>
                    <bibl><ptr target="#oliverioDAI2"/>, p. 118, n. <citedRange>122</citedRange>, fig. 78a</bibl>, whence 
                    <bibl><ptr target="#SEG"/>, <citedRange>9.234</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>027800</citedRange></bibl>.
                    Cf. <bibl><ptr target="#cassels1955"/>, p. <citedRange>21</citedRange></bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#beschi1970"/>, pp. <citedRange>199, 204</citedRange> (date of the base)</bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#dthorn-thorn2009"/>, p. <citedRange>69</citedRange></bibl> (Cassels' notebook);
                    <bibl><ptr target="#santucci2010"/>, pp. <citedRange>279-280</citedRange> and fig. 4a</bibl> (location);
                    <bibl><ptr target="#belzic2022"/>, catalogue <citedRange>B.11</citedRange></bibl> (corresponding half-statue).</p>
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><persName type="attested" key="http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?id=V1-65566"><name nymRef="#Σάτυρος">Σάτυρος</name>
                    <lb n="2"/><persName type="attested" key="http://clas-lgpn2.classics.ox.ac.uk/cgi-bin/lgpn_search.cgi?id=V1-65506"><name type="patronymic" nymRef="#Πρώταρχος">Πρωτάρχου</name></persName></persName>
	 </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p/>
 </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="fr" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Satyros fils de Protarkhos.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="en" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Satyros son of Protarchos.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:lang="it" xml:space="preserve">
            <p>Satyros figlio di Protarchos.</p>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>Satyros son of Protarchos should have been the first to be buried in that tomb. The original funerary half-figure was later substituted 
                    by a stele for a deceased veteran (<ref type="inscription" target="https://ircyr2020.inslib.kcl.ac.uk/en/inscriptions/C.573.html">IRCyr2020 C.573</ref>).</p>
	           <p>The name Satyros has here its only occurrence in Cyrenaica. The father's name is non-dialectal, both for the ending of genitive in <foreign xml:lang="grc">-ου</foreign> 
	           and for the first member of the compound <foreign xml:lang="grc">Πρωτ(ο)-</foreign> instead of dialectal <foreign xml:lang="grc">Πρατ(ο)-</foreign>. As no ethnic is given, he might have been a Cyrenaen 
	           with foreign connections.</p>
	<p/>
            </div></body>
